                          throws ApiException
        Build call for searchV2
        Parameters:
        searchText - The input to be searched. (required)
        latitude - Latitude of the location. We need to make sure that either Lat/Lng or Country is provided to API (optional)
        longitude - Longitude of the location. We need to make sure that either Lat/Lng or Country is provided to API (optional)
        searchRadius - Radius range within which search is performed. (optional)
        searchRadiusUnit - Radius unit such as Feet, Kilometers, Miles or Meters. (optional)
        maxCandidates - Maximum number of POIs that can be retrieved. (optional)
        country - Country ISO code. We need to make sure that either Lat/Lng or Country is provided to API (optional)
        matchOnAddressNumber - Option so that we force api to match on address number (optional)
        autoDetectLocation - Option to allow API to detect origin of API request automatically (optional)
        ipAddress - (optional)
        areaName1 - State province of the input to be searched (optional)
        areaName3 - City of the input to be searched (optional)
        postCode - Postal Code of the input to be searched (optional)
        returnAdminAreasOnly - if value set 'Y' then it will only do a matching on postcode or areaName1, areaName2, areaName3 and areaName4 fields in the data (optional)
        includeRangesDetails - if value set 'Y' then display all unit info of ranges, if value set 'N' then don't show ranges (optional)
        searchType - Preference to control search type of interactive requests. (optional)
        searchOnAddressNumber - Preference to search on address number. (optional)
        _callback - Callback for upload/download progress
        Returns:
        Call to execute
        Throws:
        ApiException - If fail to serialize the request body object
